    "The following are equivalent: (i) δ i 0 j 0 ∶ a → a -i 0 is a BP-map (ii) δ i 0 j 0 a = a -i 0 (iii) A i 0 ⊂ A j 0, (iv) δ i 0 j 0 ∶ a → a is an SP-map Notations A.2.3 We denote by PSITE i 0 j 0 (I, A) the set of all p-sites on (I, A) such that A i 0 ⊂ A j 0.The p-sites of PSITE i 0 j 0 (I, A) are those where the delegation δ i 0 j 0 results in the withdrawal of i 0, the delegation does not modify the aspirations of the delegate.Proposition A.2.4 Let δ i 0 j 0 ∶ I → I be a delegation function.",
